rComments: She's kind of a quirky funny lady, but she makes you work to get an A. Discussion is mandatory. Class is not, but I suggest going because she offers extra credit here and there.

This class was a bit challenging. Required a lot of studying. She's not the most intelligent professor common sense wise, and I taught most of the class to myself. The sample exams helped me get an A in the class.

She live streams all of the lectures thus when it's 20 degrees and snowing you don't even have to leave your dorm or feel bad about skipping lecture. All her notes are posted online and she's relatively helpful if you have questions.

Easily one of the worst math professors I've ever had. She is constantly making mistakes during lecture. Lecture doesn't even help, I have to self teach myself with the book. Plus, her voice is so annoying you will want to scream. I haven't met a single student in Math 125 who enjoys her.
She is really friendly and soooo clear!  Her lectures are great, and she even records them and puts the videos up so you can watch them later and review.
